---
import SiteHeader from "../../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../../components/SiteFooter.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | DragonFruit"
  description="How DragonFruit collects, uses, stores, and protects personal data."
  canonicalPath="/legal/privacy"
>
  <main class="essay-shell legal-page">
    <header class="home-header legal-header">
      <SiteHeader />
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="home-section home-intro legal-content">
      <p>
        Last updated May 27, 2026. This policy explains how DragonFruit collects, uses, stores, shares, and protects
        personal data, including data accessed through Google Sign-In and Google Calendar.
      </p>

      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        DragonFruit is a workspace for projects, tasks, docs, meeting notes, stickies, and agent-assisted work. This
        policy applies to DragonFruit&apos;s web app, API, and companion experiences.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Account information such as name, email address, profile image, and authentication data.</li>
        <li>Workspace content such as projects, tasks, docs, comments, settings, and agent activity.</li>
        <li>Technical information such as device, browser, IP address, logs, and diagnostic events.</li>
        <li>Voice note content when you choose to record or dictate notes.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Google User Data</h2>
      <p>
        If you sign in with Google, DragonFruit may access your Google account identifier, email, name, and profile
        image for authentication. If you connect Google Calendar, DragonFruit may access event metadata needed to show
        meetings and organize related work.
      </p>

      <h2>Google API Services Limited Use</h2>
      <p>
        DragonFruit&apos;s use and transfer of information received from Google APIs follows the Google API Services User
        Data Policy, including Limited Use requirements. DragonFruit does not sell Google user data, does not use it
        for advertising, and does not use it to train general-purpose AI models.
      </p>

      <h2>BYOK and AI Providers</h2>
      <p>
        If you connect third-party AI providers using BYOK, DragonFruit may process prompts, outputs, and related
        metadata to provide the feature. Provider-side processing is governed by each provider&apos;s terms and privacy
        policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Sharing, Security, and Retention</h2>
      <p>
        DragonFruit shares data only as needed to provide the service, maintain security, prevent abuse, and comply
        with law. We apply reasonable safeguards for data in transit and at rest, and retain data while your account is
        active or as needed to provide the service.
      </p>

      <h2>Open-source License</h2>
      <p>
        DragonFruit includes software licensed under AGPL-3.0. Source code for the running version is available at
        <a href="https://github.com/miguelreng/DragonFruit" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          github.com/miguelreng/DragonFruit
        </a>
        .
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions or deletion requests, contact
        <a href="mailto:miguelreng@gmail.com">miguelreng@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <SiteFooter />
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
